    "Linear independence of the E X b,j;a,i also follows from this.That this set of matrix units is complete follows from the identification of Tube S witha∈Irr C C(a ⊗ χ ⊗S → χ ⊗S ⊗ a) ≃ X∈Irr Z(C) C(χ ⊗S → X *) ⊗ C(X → χ ⊗S),where this isomorphism is provided in Lemma 7.4 of [39].",
    "□ The TQFT inner productThe skein modules A(Σ) are the state spaces of the Turaev-Viro-Barrett-Westbury TQFT [43,44].",
    "Since C is unitary one can use the TQFT partition function Z to equip these skein modules with an inner product as follows (see [37,38]).Recall that the partition function Z assigns a complex number Z(M; x) to any 3-manifold M with a string diagram x ∈ S(∂M) on its boundary.",
    "In fact, Z(M; x) depends only on the equivalence class of x in A(∂M) so we have a linear map Z M: A(∂M) → C for each 3-manifold M. Since any 3-manifold admits a handle decomposition, the partition function is completely determined by the following normalisation, gluing, and product properties:• For the 3-ball B and a string diagram x on the 2-sphere ∂B we haveZ B (x) = ev(x),where ev(x) interprets x as a diagram in the plane and uses the graphical calculus of C to evaluate that diagram to a number ([39, Theorem 2.4], [44]).• If M gl is obtained from a 3-manifold M with boundary ∂M = N ∪ N ∪ L by gluing N to N then [37, Section 4]Z M gl (x gl) = e Z M (x ∪ e ∪ ê) (e, e),(14)where the sum ranges over an orthogonal basis of A(N; b), with b the boundary condition induced by x.• If M = M 1 ⊔ M 2 is a disjoint union and x = x 1 ⊔ x 2 is a string diagram on ∂M with x 1 on ∂M 1 and x 2 on ∂M 2 then Z M (x) = Z M 1 (x 1)Z M 2 (x 2).We can use the partition function to define an inner product on the skein module A(Σ) as follows.",
